An OU (Organizational Unit) is basically a container inside Active Directory used to organize objects like:

Users 👤
Computers 💻
Groups 👥

Think of it like folders in your file system.

We use OU to separate different types of user, systems. Then we can apply single policy to whole OU.

GROUP POLICY OBJECT (GPO)
A GPO is the set of rules applied to user or computers. It detemines what a user can do and what a system can do.
There are two types of setting in GPO
1. User configuration: Applies to user no matter where he logs
2. System Configuration: Applies to system  no matter who logs in
When user logs in pollicy applies in following manner
L - Local
S -  System
D - Domain
OU - Organizational Unit
Last applied is strongest
OU policies override Domain policies
Child OU inherits parent OU policy by default
samba-tool ou create "OU=Students,DC=iot,DC=local"      # DC stands for Domain Compoent meaninig if domain is iot.local then DC=iot and DC=local
samba-tool gpo create "Student-Restrictions"

samba-tool gpo setlink "OU=Students,DC=iot,DC=local" "Student-Restrictions"
# List all gpo
samba-tool gpo listall
# Check if gpo is linked
samba-tool gpo listlinks "OU=Students,DC=iot,DC=local"
# Move user to OU
samba-tool user move student1 "OU=Students,DC=iot,DC=local"

